parameters:
Dayley Shrine Maiden: What a nice place, it's so clean. It's
a big difference from the sea at the harbor.

Thief Nora: This is the grave of a beastman child. Cors-san
wanted to show me at least a beautiful place.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: Do you know about the Island of
Prostitution? I used to be a prostitute there.
Dayley Shrine Maiden: To me, the sea was like a prison.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: One day, I thought about dying, so
after finishing my morning [duty], I tried to jump into the
sea.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: And then, the sea was so beautiful
that it felt like the sky and the sea were connected, and
the world was dyed in a single shade of blue.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: I wanted to show you, maybe something
would have changed a little...

Thief Nora: Um... why was that child committing murder over
and over again?

Dayley Shrine Maiden: I guess they all saw me as a Tragos,
someone who they could keep as a pet because of my wealthy
attire.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: I understood a little bit about this
child's thoughts and consciousness.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: Goddess Dayley is a special goddess,
she is the protector of criminals and prostitutes.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: That's why I should be the savior of
those who are truly troubled and suffering.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: Hey, would you take this person with
you?
Thief Nora: ...Is it about the clothes?

Dayley Shrine Maiden: This is the attire that praises the
goddess Dayley. It is allowed for the Dayley Shrine Maiden's
collaborator to wear it.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: I feel like you would fight for the
weak and those who are truly suffering.

Thief Nora: Understood. I will do my best to become worthy
of this attire!
実績 女神デイレーの装束

Dayley Shrine Maiden: Hey, can I take a quick look at the
sea?
Dayley Shrine Maiden: It really is a nice place...
Thief Nora: Yes, it's a beautiful place.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: I'm starting to understand the true
meaning of the shrine maiden's mission.

Dayley Shrine Maiden: I'm sorry for not being able to do
anything.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Thief Nora: Are you in charge of managing the flowers, by
any chance?
Cors the Wanderer: Well, it's just an excuse to slack off.

Cors the Wanderer: I have a rough idea why everyone has come
here.

Cors the Wanderer: So, this means that the war between the
Queen's faction and the Prince's faction is finally
starting, right?
Thief Nora: Yes, that's how we're gathering our forces.

Cors the Wanderer: As I mentioned before, most of the
organization is on the Queen's faction. They don't want
Mucos to be turned into a sea of fire.

Cors the Wanderer: In addition, the Imperial Army has
General Atu. In every aspect, the chances of the Prince's
faction winning are slim.
Thief Nora: But, didn't they say that we will win?

Cors the Wanderer: I'm just a gambler, you know. As an
organization, we're just sitting back and waiting to see who
wins, then we'll just flatter the victor.
Thief Nora: If I ask for your cooperation, will you help me?

Cors the Wanderer: Haha, jokes aside, I absolutely don't
want to go to the front lines unless it's for rear support.

Cors the Wanderer: It's like proving that I'm on the
Prince's faction, you know.

Cors the Wanderer: According to rumors... it seems that the
vicinity of the Fotizona Palace will become a battlefield.

Thief Nora: I don't understand the complicated details, but
I heard that we're doing this to avoid a civil war.
Thief Nora: Um, the conversation isn't over yet...!
Cors the Wanderer: I won't let the children die.

Cors the Wanderer: The royal palace is connected to the
Fotizona Boulevard, right? There must be a considerable
number of children living there, right?

Cors the Wanderer: From the start, I don't have the option
to choose. I really don't want to go, you know...

Cors the Wanderer: I made a promise to this grave and to
you, so I have to keep my word as a small-time thug.
Thief Nora: So, you're coming with me!

Cors the Wanderer: I don't want to cooperate, but... for the
personal promise I made with you, I'll go to the
battlefield.

Cors the Wanderer: Well, as you can see, my body is quite
poor, so being a shield is about the most I can do, but even
a small-time thug like me has some pride.

Cors the Wanderer: Well, then, I'll need to make some
preparations.

Thief Nora: I don't think I can ever forgive you, Cors-san.
I don't think you even want to be forgiven.

Thief Nora: It may sound strange, but... that's why I
believe you will definitely come to keep your promise.
Clea: As I thought, it's a beautiful view, isn't it?

Thief Nora: Yes, I would be happy if that child is also
pleased.
